==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Acupressure
<hw>Ac`u*pres"sure</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>acus</ets> needle + <ets>premere</ets>, <ets>pressum</ets>, to
press.]</ety> <fld>(Surg.)</fld> <def>A mode of arresting hemorrhage
resulting from wounds or surgical operations, by passing under the
divided vessel a needle, the ends of which are left exposed externally
on the cutaneous surface.</def> <rj><au>Simpson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Acupuncturation</ent>⟦br⟧
